#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""Manage resume actions, completed-task history, and the session-task queue.

Three distinct layers of task coordination:

  1. session-task set/clear -- single "top-of-mind" slot for the NEXT resume
     action. There is only one at a time. Lives in resume-action.json.

  2. session-task queue ... -- a cross-session work queue with scope-based
     serialization groups. Any number of items. Items in the same scope group
     run one-at-a-time (priority + FIFO). Items in disjoint groups run in
     parallel. Lives in queue.json (with fcntl.flock on every RMW).

  3. TaskCreate / TaskList / TaskUpdate (harness primitive, not in this tool)
     -- tracks background PROCESSES (unix agents/watchers/scans).

Completed items from both layers 1 and 2 are logged to completed-tasks.jsonl.

Usage:
    session-task set "description"
    session-task get | show | clear | append "..."
    session-task complete "description"
    session-task history [-n N]

    session-task queue add "desc" --scope file:~/foo --scope repo:bar \\
        [--summary "~10 word headline"] [--priority N] [--context JSON] \\
        [--created-by WHO] [--depends-on q-AAA,q-BBB]
    session-task queue list [--ready] [--all] [--group g-X] [--json]
    session-task queue show <id>
    session-task queue scope <id>
    session-task queue groups [--json]
    session-task queue ready [--json]
    session-task queue done <id>
    session-task queue abandon <id> [--reason TEXT]
    session-task queue pop [--id ID]
    session-task queue register <id> [--pid N]   # claim item for spawn (gated)
    session-task queue heartbeat <id> [--pid N]  # refresh liveness on running item
    session-task queue spawn-check <id> [--json] # "am I clear to spawn?" check
    session-task queue force-start <id> --reason TEXT  # MANUAL OVERRIDE: promote
                                                       # blocked-pending to running
    session-task queue promote <id>
    session-task queue set-summary <id> "text"   # edit one-line summary
    session-task queue depend <id> [--add q-AAA[,q-BBB]] [--remove q-CCC]
                                   [--clear] [--json]
    session-task queue prune [--older-than DURATION] [-n/--dry-run]
    session-task queue banner
    session-task queue migrate --from FILE [--yes]

Spawn gating (2026-04-17):
    Before spawning an agent, the main loop MUST go through the queue:
        1. `session-task queue add "desc" --scope <toks>` -> get id + ready_now
        2. If ready_now=false, DO NOT spawn. Wait for blockers to clear.
        3. `session-task queue spawn-check <id>` -> ok|conflict
        4. `session-task queue register <id>` -> atomically claim (running)
        5. Spawn the agent.
        6. On completion: `session-task queue done <id>` (or abandon).
    `queue register` refuses if the item isn't pending+ready, or if any
    other running item has overlapping scope (cross-group conflict).
    This is the one enforcement point. Bypassing it == operating outside
    the queue, which Andrew has flagged as a rule violation.
"""

